SB248 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to public K-12 education; to amend Section
5 16-1-20.6, Code of Alabama 1975; to further provide for the
6 provision of released time for religious instruction during
7 the school day.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
9 Section 1. Section 16-1-20.6, Code of Alabama 1975, is
10 amended to read as follows:
11 "§16-1-20.6
12 (a) This section shall be known and may be cited as the
13 Alabama Released Time Credit Act.
14 (b) The Legislature finds and declares all of the
15 following:
16 (1) That the United States Supreme Court, in its
17 decision in Zorach v. Clauson, 343 U.S. 306 (1952), upheld the
18 constitutionality of released time programs for religious
19 instruction for public school students during the school day.
20 (2) That the United States Constitution and state law
21 allows local school districts to offer religious released time
22 education for the benefit of public school students.
23 (3) That the purpose of this section is to incorporate
24 a constitutionally acceptable method of allowing school
25 districts to offer accommodate religious released time classes
26 and, in grades where credit is earned, to award students
27 elective credit for classes taken during the school day in
28 released time programs.
Page 1

released time programs.
SB248 Enrolled
29 (c) For the purposes of thisAs used in this section,
30 the following terms have the following meaningsterm released
31 time means a:
32 (1) RELEASED TIME. A period of time during the school
33 day when a student is allowed to participate in religious
34 released time instruction that is an elective course in
35 religious instruction, conducted off school district property,
36 by a private and conducted by a sponsoring entity.
37 (2) SPONSORING ENTITY. A church or other local
38 community-based religious organization.
39 (d)(1) The State Board of Education and each local
40 board of education shall allow a parent or guardian to choose
41 for his or her student to attend a religious released time
42 program conducted by a sponsoring entity.
43 (2) Subdivision (1) shall not apply in either of the
44 following circumstances:
45 a. If a local board of education or the local
46 superintendent or designee of the local board of education has
47 a reasonable belief based on objective evidence that
48 permitting a student to attend a released time program would
49 pose a substantial risk of physical harm to the student or
50 that the sponsoring entity is in violation of state law in a
51 manner that poses a substantial risk of physical harm to a
52 student.
53 b. If the student's participation in religious released
54 time would cause the student to be excused from the minimum
55 instructional time for any course or subject as prescribed by
56 the State Board of Education, or from any student intervention
Page 2

the State Board of Education, or from any student intervention
SB248 Enrolled
57 required under state or federal law, for purposes of
58 participating in religious released time.
59 (3) Nothing in this section shall be construed to:
60 a. Endorse any religious belief, practice, or
61 instruction by the State Board of Education or any local board
62 of education;
63 b. Limit the authority of local boards of education
64 over the development of school schedules; or
65 c. Limit the authority of local boards of education to
66 tailor the policies addressed in this section to meet their
67 specific needs, provided that the policy reflects the
68 requirements of this section and complies with applicable law,
69 rules, and regulations.
70 (e) The State Board of Education shall adopt and each
71 local board of education may implement adopt a policy for a
72 student to attend released time which may require that any of
73 the following as an elective course if all of the following
74 are be satisfied by the sponsoring entity:
75 (1) The parent or guardian of the student gives written
76 consent for the student to participate in religious released
77 time and completes the local board of education's standard
78 checkout authorization form for the released time program. A
79 single completed authorization form shall apply for the full
80 duration of the school year and may not be required for each
81 individual released time session.
82 (2) Released time instruction and activities are not
83 sponsored by the local board of education and do not fall
84 under the supervision, control, or authority of the local
Page 3

under the supervision, control, or authority of the local
SB248 Enrolled
85 board of education or its employees.
86 (3) The sponsoring entity maintains attendance records
87 and makes them available to the public school the student
88 attends.
89 (4)(3) The sponsoring entity makes provisions for and
90 assumes liability for the student who is excused for released
91 time.
92 (5)(4) No public funds are expended other than de
93 minimis administrative costs.
94 (6)(5) No public school personnel are involved in
95 providing the religious instruction.
96 (7) The sponsoring entity conducts a criminal history
97 background check for all employees or contractors of the
98 entity who are likely to have direct, ongoing contact with a
99 student who is excused for released time.
100 (8) The student assumes responsibility for any missed
101 school work.
102 (f)(e) In grades where credit is earned, a student who
103 participates in released time may earn elective course credit
104 for participation, as provided by rules adopted by the State
105 Board of Education for elective courses. Credit awarded may
106 not exceed normal credit given for an elective course in the
107 particular school system. The State Board of Education shall
108 also adopt minimum standards for class attendance necessary to
109 qualify for credit.
110 (g)(f) A student who participates in religious
111 instruction for elective credit during released time shall be
112 credited with time spent as if the student attended school,
Page 4

credited with time spent as if the student attended school,
SB248 Enrolled
113 and the time shall be calculated as part of the actual school
114 day.
115 (h)(g) Transportation to and from the place of released
116 time, including transportation for any student with
117 disabilities, is the complete responsibility of the sponsoring
118 private entity, parent, guardian, or student and may not be
119 arranged, coordinated, or provided for by public school
120 personnel.
121 (h) No student may be released from a required core
122 curriculum class to attend released time."
123 Section 2. This act shall become effective on July 1,
124 2026.
